com.here.android.mpa.mapping

Class MapOverlay

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.here.android.mpa.mapping.MapOverlay

  • public class MapOverlay
extends java.lang.Object
    The MapOverlay class can be used to display custom Android View-based content at a fixed location on the map.

    To use, create a MapOverlay with the custom view you wish to display and the position at which the view should be displayed. The overlay should be then added to the map with Map.addMapOverlay(MapOverlay) method. The overlay will be automatically repositioned on the screen as the map moves.

    The MapOverlay's view has performance overhead compared to a MapMarker. For use cases which only require static images, MapMarker should be used. This class should be used if features provided by View are required, such as animation or dynamic content.

    For rarely updating of MapOverlay, the manual refresh mode can be used. Method MapOverlay.setManualRefresh(boolean) replaces the MapOverlay's view with static "snapshot" of the view to improve performance during frequent map movements.

    Note, during frequent map updates (for example during navigation) view's might blink. To avoid this use MapOverlay.setManualRefresh(boolean) method.
    See Also:
    Map.addMapOverlay(MapOverlay), Map.removeMapOverlay(MapOverlay)

    • Method Detail

      • getAnchorPoint

        public android.graphics.PointF getAnchorPoint()
        Returns the anchor point for this MapOverlay.

        The overlay is drawn with the specified pixel offset from its MapOverlay.getCoordinate() position.

        By default, there is no offset and the MapOverlay anchor is positioned in the center of the overlay.

        Returns:
        The current MapOverlay anchor point.

      • setAnchorPoint

        public MapOverlay setAnchorPoint(android.graphics.PointF anchor)
        Sets an anchor point for this MapOverlay.

        The overlay is drawn with the specified pixel offset from its MapOverlay.getCoordinate() position. To clear an anchor set previously, pass a PointF to this method with an X-coordinate equal to half the width of the view and a Y-coordinate equal to half the height of the view.

        By default, there is no offset and the MapOverlay anchor is positioned in the center of the overlay.

        Parameters:
        anchor - A PointF relative to the top-left corner of the MapOverlay.
        Returns:
        The updated MapOverlay itself.

      • refresh

        public void refresh()
        Updates MapOverlay's view when it behaves in manual refresh mode. In that case static image will be updated to reflect last changes on the MapOverlay's view.
        See Also:

      • setManualRefresh

        public void setManualRefresh(boolean manualRefresh)
        Sets manual refresh mode for MapOverlay's view. MapOverlay's view on the map starts behaving similarly to MapMarker. Static snapshot of the overlay is made at the time when this method is called with true parameter and is used each time when the map moves. To update the MapOverlay's view, call the MapOverlay.refresh() method.

        Note, there are known limitations when manual refresh mode is set to true. As there will not be view on the map but snapshot of it, operation such as animation can not be performed. Also snapshots for some views will not be that accurate(e.g. view's shadow will be missing). If it is needed to have click listener on the view, developer must register it on the provided view(all other click listeners of the view's children will not be active), only then SDK will redirect click event on the snapshot to the click listener of the provided view.

        Parameters:
        manualRefresh - Set true to enable manual refresh for MapOverlay's view, otherwise false to switch back to normal behavior of MapOverlay's view.
        See Also:
        MapOverlay.refresh()

      • isManualRefresh

        public boolean isManualRefresh()
        Returns a boolean value indicating whether MapOverlay's view is set to be manually refreshed using MapOverlay.refresh() method.
        Returns:
        True if MapOverlay's view is manually refreshed, false otherwise
